+### 2026-03-08 - Phase 0 Map Migration Surface (`migration-batch`)
+
+#### Scope Scanned
+- `/Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Web-Frontend/src/routes/AppRoutes.jsx`
+- `/Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/ListingPage`
+- `/Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/UserSetting`
+- `/Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/HajjGuidance/HajjGuidance.jsx`
+- Shared booking/user-setting feature hooks and utilities that currently control route handoff:
+  - `src/features/booking/hooks/useBookingLogic.js`
+  - `src/features/paymentMethods/hooks/usePaymentMethodsLogic.js`
+  - `src/features/travelersInfo/hooks/useTravelersInfoLogic.js`
+  - `src/features/remainingPayment/hooks/useRemainingPaymentLogic.js`
+  - `src/features/bookingStatus/hooks/useBookingStatusData.js`
+  - `src/features/booking/utils/bookingFlowUtils.js`
+  - `src/features/packageDetail/hooks/usePackageBookingAction.js`
+
+#### Migration Surface Inventory
+| Target | Current split pattern | Shared state/contracts already present | Migration notes |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Listing | `src/pages/ListingPage/ListingPage.js` renders a desktop shell and delegates mobile to `src/pages/ListingPage/ListingMobileScreen.jsx` behind `hidden lg:block` / `block lg:hidden`. | `useListingPageData`, `FiltersComponent`, `ListingSearchInput`, `ListingResultsPanel`, listing sort/filter config. | Data ownership is already unified; remaining work is presentational consolidation into one responsive content tree. |
+| Booking setup | `src/pages/UserSetting/MyApplication/Booking/booking.jsx` and `src/pages/UserSetting/MyApplication/Mobile/mobilebooking.jsx` are both large route-grade files and both create their own `useBookingLogic()` instance. | `useBookingLogic`, `BookingDateSelector`, `BookingInvoiceBreakdown`, `BookingErrorAlert`, `bookingFlowUtils`, `usePackageBookingAction`. | Highest-risk pair because duplicate hook ownership can drift selected date, traveler groups, and payment handoff if only one side is updated. |
+| Booking status | `src/pages/UserSetting/MyApplication/Booking/bookingstatus.jsx` renders desktop chrome and imports `../Mobile/bookingstatus`; mobile keeps a second booking-card layout. | `useBookingStatusData`, `BookingStatusFilterSelect`, `BookingStatusPagination`, `bookingStatusUtils`, `BookingCard`. | Good candidate for one responsive page because route/navigation rules already live in shared utilities. |
+| Payment methods | `src/pages/UserSetting/PaymentMethods/paymentMethods.jsx` already uses one `PaymentPageContent` plus one `usePaymentMethodsLogic()` instance for both desktop and mobile shells. | `usePaymentMethodsLogic`, `PaymentActionCard`, `PaymentOrderSummaryCard`, `BankDetailsCard`, `PaymentMethodSelector`, `Stepper`, `MobileStepper`. | This page is the closest to target state and should be treated as the reference pattern for the rest of the flow. |
+| Traveler details | `src/pages/UserSetting/Datatable/datatable.jsx` owns the route and passes `travelersState` into `src/pages/UserSetting/Datatable/Mobile/datatable.jsx`. | `useTravelersInfoLogic`, traveler modals, `TravelersInfoTable`, `TravelersInfoMobileList`, traveler pagination/save components. | Shared hook/state already exists; remaining migration is shell unification and collapsing mobile-only list/table branches. |
+| Remaining payment | `src/pages/UserSetting/RemainingPayment/remainingPayment.jsx` owns the route and passes `remainingPaymentState` into `src/pages/UserSetting/RemainingPayment/Mobile/remainingPayment.jsx`. | `useRemainingPaymentLogic`, `RemainingPaymentSummaryCard`, shared payment form components. | Shared state is already centralized; preserve the `booking_number` query/state bridge while collapsing the breakpoint split. |
+| Operator response | `src/pages/UserSetting/OperatorResponse/operatorresponse.jsx` and `src/pages/UserSetting/OperatorResponse/Mobile/operatorresponse.jsx` each fetch bookings and each recompute payment/booking status logic. | `fetchBookingsByUser` only; no dedicated feature hook exists yet. | Needs extraction before JSX cleanup, otherwise desktop/mobile status logic will continue to drift. |
+| Payment and wallet | `src/pages/UserSetting/Payment&Wallet/payment&wallet.jsx` and `src/pages/UserSetting/Payment&Wallet/Mobile/paymentwallet.jsx` both fetch profile + transactions and both own transfer/withdraw modal state. | Shared APIs only: `getProfileData`, `getAllWalletTransactions`, `createBankDetails`, `createWithdrawRequest`. | No feature module exists yet; this is another extraction-first migration target. |
+| Wishlist | `src/pages/UserSetting/Wishlist/index.jsx` uses `window.innerWidth` to choose `wishlist.jsx` or `wishlistMobile.jsx`; desktop `wishlist.jsx` also renders the mobile page under `lg:hidden`. | Shared APIs only: `getShortPackageDetails`; shared localStorage contract: `savedPackages`. | Current pattern is brittle and double-branches at both route and page level. Replace with one route owner before deleting mobile files. |
+| Messages | `/messages` points to `src/pages/UserSetting/Message/messagePage.jsx`, which renders desktop `message.jsx` and mobile `Mobile/Message/messagepageview.jsx`; `/messages-chat` points to `src/pages/UserSetting/Message/messagechat.jsx`. | No backend chat feature hook; current conversations are hard-coded UI state in desktop/mobile files. | This surface is structurally inconsistent even before responsive cleanup. Phase 1 should decide whether `/messages-chat` stays as a compatibility subroute or collapses into `/messages`. |
+| Hajj Guidance | `src/pages/HajjGuidance/HajjGuidance.jsx` is a single file but still contains an inline `block lg:hidden` mobile-only card list while the rest of the page manually composes `Header` and `Footer`. | No shared feature hook; content arrays already live in-page. | This is lower risk than booking/payment pages, but it still violates the one-page-one-responsive-system rule and bypasses `BrandPageShell`. |
+
+#### Route and Dependency Boundaries That Must Move Together
+- Route owners and aliases:
+  - `/bookings` and `/package-booking` both point to `MyApplication/Booking/booking.jsx`.
+  - `/booking-page` points to `PackageDetailPage/Mobile/components/invoice`, and `SidebarMenu` still treats it as part of the booking flow.
+  - `/payment-wallet-mobile` points directly to `Payment&Wallet/Mobile/paymentwallet.jsx`.
+  - `/messages-chat` is still a standalone route beside `/messages`.
+- Booking flow contracts already centralized in shared utilities:
+  - `usePackageBookingAction` decides when package detail should navigate to `/package-booking`.
+  - `useBookingLogic` advances to `/payment-methods`.
+  - `usePaymentMethodsLogic` advances to `/data-table`.
+  - `useTravelersInfoLogic` advances to `/remaining-payment` or `/operator-response`.
+  - `useRemainingPaymentLogic` advances to `/operator-response`.
+- User-setting chrome dependencies currently duplicated across the scope:
+  - `SidebarMenu`
+  - `Stepper`
+  - `MobileStepper`
+  - `Header`
+  - `BrandPageShell` is used only on some of the newer responsive pages and should become the shell baseline for route-level public/account pages where appropriate.
+
+#### Desired Target Pattern
+- One route component per user-facing route, with responsive layout handled inside a single page structure.
+- Keep flow logic in shared hooks and utilities, not in duplicated mobile/desktop route files.
+- Convert `/booking-page` and `/payment-wallet-mobile` into compatibility aliases that render or redirect to the unified responsive route until internal references are removed.
+- Normalize user-setting pages around a reusable responsive account shell so sidebar/stepper/header treatment stops diverging per page.
+- Treat `paymentMethods.jsx` as the reference implementation because it already shares one content component and one state owner across breakpoints.
+
+#### Compatibility Risks and Rollback Requirements
+- Do not remove `/booking-page` or `/payment-wallet-mobile` during the first implementation pass; both are still declared in `AppRoutes.jsx`, and `/booking-page` is still included in `SidebarMenu` activity detection.
+- Do not break `location.state` and query-string handoff for `bookingNumber`, `invoiceData`, `remainingAmount`, `transactionAmount`, and `booking_number`; those values currently bridge every step of the booking/payment/traveler/operator-response flow.
+- Booking setup, operator response, wallet, wishlist, and messages all still have duplicated mobile/desktop state ownership. Extract shared state first, then collapse layout trees.
+- Wishlist currently uses `window.innerWidth` in `Wishlist/index.jsx`; remove that branch only after the unified page is stable, otherwise resize and initial-render behavior can diverge.
+- Messages has route ambiguity between `/messages` and `/messages-chat` plus mock-only data. If Phase 1 changes structure there, keep a compatibility path until the final route contract is explicit.
+- Safe rollback boundary: migrate in route-family order, keep legacy mobile files until the unified route compiles and static route tracing shows that navigation targets and imports are unchanged.

